obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (24173)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1998, s. 3, for "(conditions of service)" (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24173&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the High Court Judges ^1`
  line `[(Salaries and Conditions of Service)]`
  line `Act, 1954.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (24174)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24174&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "acting Chief Justice" means a Judge appointed under article 223 of the Constitution to`
  line `perform the duties of the Chief Justice;`
  line
  line `(b) "acting Judge" means a person ^1*** appointed to act as a Judge ^2*** ^3[under clause (2) of`
  line `article 224 of the Constitution];`
  line
  line `(c) "actual service" includes`
  line
  line `(i) time spent by a Judge on duty as a Judge or in the performance of such other functions as`
  line `he may, at the request of the President of India, undertake to discharge;`
  line
  line `(ii) vacations, excluding any time during which the Judge is absent on leave;`
  line
  line `(iii) Joining time on transfer from a High Court to the Supreme Court or from one High Court`
  line `to another or from the Supreme Court to a High Court;`
  line
  line `(iv) time spent by a Judge on duty as a Judge of a former Indian High Court;`
  line
  line `(v) time spent by a Judge to attend the sittings of the Supreme Court as an ad hoc Judge under`
  line `article 127 of the Constitution; and`
  line
  line `(vi) vacation (excluding any time during which the Judge was absent on leave) taken by a`
  line `Judge as a Judge of a former Indian High Court;br`
  line
  line `(d) "additional Judge" means a person ^1*** appointed as an additional Judge ^4*** ^5[under`
  line `clause (1) of article 224 of the Constitution];`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `(f) "High Court" means a High Court ^7[for a State] and includes a High Court which was`
  line `exercising Jurisdiction ^8[in a Part A State or] in the corresponding Province before the`
  line `commencement of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(g) "Judge" means a Judge of a High Court and includes the Chief Justice ^9[an acting Chief`
  line `Justice, an additional Judge and an acting Judge of the High Court];`
  line
  line `^10[(gg) "pension" means a pension of any kind whatsoever payable to or in respect of a Judge, and`
  line `includes any gratuity or other sum or sums so payable by way of death or retirement benefits;]`
  line
  line `(h) service for pension includes`
  line
  line `(i) actual service;`
  line
  line `^11[(ii) the amount, actually taken, of each period of leave on full allowances at a rate equal to`
  line `the monthly rate of the salary;]`
  line
  line `(iii) joining time on return from leave out of India;`
  line
  line `(i) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In the calculation of service for the purposes of this Act, ^12[service for any period or periods as`
  line `acting Judge or additional Judge] shall be reckoned as service as a Judge but, save as otherwise expressly`
  line `provided, previous service as an acting Chief Justice shall not be reckoned as service as Chief Justice.`
  line
  line `^13* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "who was" omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956 (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `2. The words, brackets and figures 'under sub-section (2) of section 222 of the Government of India Act, 1935 or" Omitted by`
  line `Act 13 of 2016, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `3. The words, brackets and figures "or under clause (2) of article 224 of the Constitution " were inserted by the Adaptation of`
  line `Laws (No.3) Order, 1956 (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `4. The words, brackets and figures "under sub-section (3) of section 222 of the Government of India Act, 1935 or" omitted by`
  line `Act 13 of 2016, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `5. The words, brackets and figures 'under clause (1) of article 224 of the Constitution' were inserted by the Adaptation of Laws`
  line `(No.3) Order, 1956 (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `6. Clause (e) omitted by Act 13 of 2016, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No.3) Order, 1956, for in any Part A State (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Adaptation of Laws (No.3) Order, 1956 (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 46 of 1958, s. 2, for and acting Chief Justice of a High Court (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 50 of 1961, s. 2 (w.e.f. 20-5-1954).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 57 of 1980, s. 2, for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 10-12-1980).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `13. Sub-sections (3) and (4) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (24175)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Kinds of leave admissible to a judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24175&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, leave granted to`
  line `a Judge may be at his option either—`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) leave on full allowances (including commuted leave on half allowances into leave or full`
  line `allowances on medical certificate); or]`
  line
  line `(b) leave on half allowances; or`
  line
  line `(c) leave partly on full allowances and partly on half allowances.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Chapter, any period of leave on full allowances shall be reckoned as`
  line `double that period of leave on half allowances.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3) For the purposes of this Chapter, casual leave may be admissible to a Judge in a calendar year,`
  line `for such number of days and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 78 of 1971, s. 3, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 15-1-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 3 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (24176)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Leave account showing the amount of leave due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24176&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A leave account shall be kept for each`
  line `Judge showing therein the amount of leave due to him in terms of leave on half allowances.`
  line
  line `(2) In the leave account of a Judge`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be credited to him`
  line
  line `(i) one-fourth of the time spent by him on actual service;^1* * *`
  line
  line `(ii) where the Judge, by reason of his having been detained for the performance of duties not`
  line `connected with the High Court, cannot enjoy any vacation which would otherwise have been`
  line `entitled to enjoy had he not been so detained, as compensation for the vacation not enjoyed, a`
  line `period equal to double the period by which the vacation enjoyed by him in any year falls short of`
  line `one month; and`
  line
  line `^2[(iii) where the Judge had, prior to his appointment as such, held any pensionable post under`
  line `the Union or a State, the period of leave earned by him in the said post, ^3* * * * *and]`
  line
  line `(b) there shall be debited to him all leave with all by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "and" omitted by Act 38 of 1986, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 38 of 1986, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-1986).`
  line
  line `3. The words “so, however, that such period shall not exceed two hundred and forty days in terms of leave on full allowances”`
  line `omitted by Act 7 of 1999, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-1-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (24177)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Leave encashment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24177&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Leave encashment.—A Judge shall be entitled in his entire service, including the period of`
  line `service rendered in a pensionable post under the Union or State or on re-employment, if any, to claim the`
  line `cash equivalent of leave salary on his retirement ^2`
  line `[in respect of the period of leave at his credit, calculated`
  line `calculated on full allowances basis,] to the extent of the maximum period prescribed for encashment of`
  line `such leave under the All India Service (Leave) Rules, 1955.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid (w.e.f. 8-1-1999).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 4, for “in respect of the period of earned leave at his credit” (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (24178)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Aggregate amount of leave which may be granted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 78 of 1971, s. 4, for "the maximum period of leave which may be granted" (w.e.f. 15-1-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24178&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The aggregate amount of leave which`
  line `may be granted to a Judge during the whole period of his service as such shall not exceed in terms of`
  line `leave on half allowances three years together with the aggregate of the periods, if any, credited to his`
  line `leave account under sub-section (2) (a) (ii) of section 4 as compensation for vacation not enjoyed.`
  line
  line `(2) The aggregate amount of leave on full allowances which may be granted to a Judge during the`
  line `whole period of his service as such shall not exceed one-twenty-fourth of the period spent by him on`
  line `actual service together with one-half of the aggregate periods, if any, credited to his leave account under`
  line `sub-section (2) (a) (ii) of section 4 as compensation for vacation not enjoyed.`
  line
  line `(3) ^1`
  line `[Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 5A, the maximum period of leave which`
  line `may be granted] at one time shall be, in the case of leave on full allowances, five months and in the case`
  line `of leave with allowances of any kind, sixteen months.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (24179)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 7
  title `Commutation of leave on half allowances into leave on full allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-1-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24179&sectionno=5A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Commutation of leave on half allowances into leave on full allowances.—(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) of section 5, a Judge may be permitted to commute`
  line `leave on half allowances into leave on full allowances on medical certificate up to a maximum of three`
  line `months during the whole period of his service as a Judge.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the maximum period of leave on full allowances which may be granted at one time`
  line `to Judge under sub-section (3) of section 5, the amount of commuted leave permitted to him under this`
  line `section shall not be taken into account.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24180)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Grant of leave not due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1958, s. 3, for "and not more than once" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24180&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the maximum limit specified in sub-section (1) of section 5,`
  line `leave on half allowances may be granted to a Judge in excess of the amount at his credit—`
  line
  line `(i) on medical certificate; or`
  line
  line `(ii) otherwise than on medical certificate, for not more than six months ^1`
  line `[or for two or more`
  line `periods, not exceeding in the aggregate, six months] during the whole period of his service as a Judge:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such leave shall be granted if the Judge is not expected to return to duty at the end of`
  line `such leave and earn the leave granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24181)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Special disability leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24181&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The rules for the time being in force with respect to the grant of special`
  line `disability leave in relation to an officer of the Central Civil Services, Class I who has entered service on`
  line `or after the 16th July, 1931 and who may be disabled by injury caused in, or in consequence of, the due`
  line `performance of his official duties or in consequence of his official position, shall apply in relation to a`
  line Judge.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24182)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Extraordinary leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24182&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[Extraordinary leave may be granted to a Judge for a period not`
  line `exceeding six months, or for two or more periods, not exceeding in the aggregate, six months] during the`
  line `whole period of his service as a Judge in excess of any leave permissible under the foregoing provisions`
  line `of this Chapter, but no salary or allowances shall be payable during, or in respect of, such leave.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1958, s. 4, for "Extraordinary leave not exceeding six months in duration may be granted to a Judge not`
  line `more than once" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24183)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Leave allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 5, for section 9 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24183&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Leave allowances.—The monthly rate of leave salary payable to a Judge shall be in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 3.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24184)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24184&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `[Allowances for joining time.]Omitted by the High Court and the Supreme Court Judges (Salaries`
  line `and Conditions of Service) Amendment Act, 2016 (13 of 2016), s. 6 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24185)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Combining leave with vacation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24185&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `A Judge may be permitted to combine vacation on full salary`
  line `with leave, if.—`
  line
  line `(a) where the vacation consists of one continuous period, the leave is taken either at the`
  line `commencement or at the end of the vacation but not a both;`
  line
  line `(b) where the vacation is divided into two separate periods, the leave is taken for the interval, or`
  line `part of the interval, between the two periods of that vacation, or for the interval, or part of the interval,`
  line `between the second period of that vacation and the commencement of the next ensuing vacation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such permission to combine vacation with leave shall be granted if it becomes`
  line `necessary to appoint an acting Chief Justice during the period of vacation or if the Judge is not expected`
  line `to return to duty at the end of such leave.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24186)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Consequences of overstaying leave or vacation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24186&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `If a Judge overstays his leave or any vacation,`
  line `whether combined with leave or not, he shall receive no salary for the period of his absence in excess of`
  line `leave granted to him or beyond the end of the vacation, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such absence is due to circumstances beyond his control, the period thereof may be`
  line `treated as leave and may be debited to his leave account.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24187)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Authority competent to grant leave, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24187&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The authority competent to grant or refuse leave to a`
  line `Judge or revoke or curtail leave granted to a Judge shall be the Governor of the State in which the`
  line `principal seat of the High Court is situate, after consultation with the Chief Justice of that High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (24188)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 16
  title `Salaries of the Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24188&sectionno=13A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 ^2[13A. Salaries of the Judges.(1) There shall be paid to the Chief Justice of a High Court, by way`
  line `of salary, ^3[ ^4[two lakh fifty thousand rupees per mensem] ].`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be paid to a Judge of a High Court, by way of salary, ^5[ ^6[two lakh twenty-five thousand rupees per`
  line mensem].]
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1998, s. 4, for "pension" (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2009, s. 2, for "thirty thousand rupees per mensem" (w.e.f. 1-1-2006).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2018, s. 2, for "ninety thousand rupees per mensem" (w.e.f. 1-1-2016).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2009, s. 2, for "twenty-six thousand rupees per mensem" (w.e.f. 1-1-2006).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 10 of 2018, s. 2, for "eighty thousand rupees per mensem" (w.e.f. 1-1-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24189)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `Pension payable to Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24189&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, every Judge shall, on his`
  line `retirement, be paid a pension in accordance with the scale and provisions in Part I of the First Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such pension shall be payable to a Judge unless—`
  line
  line `(a) he has completed not less than twelve years of service for pension; or`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(b) he has attained the age of sixty-two years; or;]`
  line
  line `(c) his retirement is medically certified to be necessitated by ill-health:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided further that if a Judge at the time of his appointment is in receipt of a pension (other than a`
  line `disability or wound pension) in respect of any previous service in the Union or a State, the pension`
  line `payable under this Act shall be in lieu of, and not in addition to, that pension.]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[Explanation.—In this section "Judge" means a Judge who has not held any other pensionable post`
  line `under the Union or a State and includes a Judge who having held any other pensionable post under the`
  line `Union or a State has elected to receive the pension payable under Part I of the First Schedule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 7 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 46 of 1958, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 7, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (24190)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 18
  title `Benefit of added years of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24190&sectionno=14A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Benefit of added years of service.—Subject to the provisions of this Act, a period of ten`
  line `years shall be added and shall be deemed to have been added from the 1st day of April, 2004 for the`
  line `purposes of pension, to the service of a Judge who is appointed as such Judge under sub-clause (b) of`
  line `clause (2) of article 217 of the Constitution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (24191)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 19
  title `Special provision of pension in respect of Judges who are members of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24191&sectionno=15&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] Every`
  line Judge—
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) who ^3`
  line `*** has held any other ^4`
  line `[pensionable post] under the Union or a State, shall on his`
  line `retirement, be paid a pension in accordance with the scale and provisions in Part III of the First`
  line `Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that every such Judge shall elect to receive the pension payable to him either under Part I of`
  line `the First Schedule or, ^5`
  line `*** Part III of the First Schedule, and the pension payable to him shall be`
  line `calculated accordingly.`
  line
  line `^6[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), any Judge to whom that sub-section`
  line `applies and who is in service on or after the 1st day of October, 1974, may, if he has elected under the`
  line `proviso to that sub-section to receive the pension payable to him under ^7*** Part III of the First Schedule`
  line `before the date on which the High Court Judges (Conditions of Service) Amendment Act, 1976 (35 of`
  line `1976) receives the assent of the President, cancel such election and elect afresh to receive the pension`
  line `payable to him under Part I of the First Schedule and any such Judge who dies before the date of such`
  line `assent shall be deemed to have elected afresh to be governed by the provisions of the said Part I if the`
  line `provisions of that Part are more favourable in his case.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 15 renumbered as sub-section (1), thereof by Act 35 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) Omitted by Act 13 of 2016, s. 9 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `3. The words “is not a member of the Indian Civil Service but” omitted by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 57 of 1980, s. 4, for “pensionable civil post” (w.e.f. 10-12-1980).`
  line
  line `5. The words and figures “as the case may be, Part II or” omitted by Act 13 of 2016, s. 9(w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 35 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1974).`
  line
  line `7.The words and figures “Part II or, as the case may be,” omitted by Act 13 of 2016, s. 9 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (24192)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of President to add to the service for pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. The words and figures “Part II or” omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24192&sectionno=16&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The President of India may for special`
  line `reasons direct that any period not exceeding three months shall be added to the service for pension of a`
  line `Judge:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period so added shall be disregarded in calculating any additional pension under`
  line `Part I or ^1*** Part III of the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (24193)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `Extraordinary pensions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24193&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The rules for the time being in force with respect to the grant of`
  line `extraordinary pensions and gratuities in relation to an officer of the Central Civil Services, Class I who`
  line `has entered service on or after the 1st April, 1937 and who may suffer injury or die as a result of violence, shall apply in relation to a Judge, subject, however, to the modification that references in those rules to`
  line `tables of injury, gratuities and pensions and of family gratuities and pensions, shall be construed as`
  line `references to the tables in the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (24194)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 22
  title `Family pensions and gratuities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24194&sectionno=17A&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[17A. Family pensions and gratuities.--`
  line `^2[ ^3[(1)] Where a Judge who, being in service on or after the`
  line `the commencement of the High Court and Supreme Court Judges (Conditions of Service) Amendment`
  line `Act, 1986 (38 of 1986), dies, whether before or after retirement in circumstances to which section 17 does`
  line `not apply, family pension calculated at the rate of ^4[fifty per cent. of his salary] ^5*** on the date of his`
  line `death shall be payable to the person or persons entitled thereto and the amount so payable shall be paid`
  line `from the day following the date of death of the Judge for a period of seven years or for a period up to the`
  line `date on which the Judge would have attained the age of sixty-five years, had he survived, whichever is`
  line `earlier, ^6[ ^7[and thereafter at the rate of thirty per cent of his salary ^8`
  line ***.]]
  line
  line `^9[Provided that in no case the amount of family pension calculated under this sub-section shall exceed`
  line `exceed the pension payable to the Judge under this Act.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of determining the person or persons entitled to family pension under`
  line `this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a Judge who elects or is eligible to receive pension under Part I of the First`
  line `Schedule, the rules, notifications and orders for the time being in force with regard to the person or`
  line `persons entitled to family pension in relation to an officer of the Central Civil Services, Group A,`
  line `shall apply;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a Judge who elects to receive pension under ^10*** Part III of the First Schedule,`
  line `the ordinary rules of his service if he had not been appointed a Judge with respect to the person or`
  line `persons entitled to family pension shall apply and his service as a Judge being treated as service`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(2) Where any Judge, who has elected to receive the pension payable to him under ^9*** Part III of the`
  line `First Schedule, retires, or dies in circumstances to which section 17 does not apply, gratuity, if any, shall`
  line `be payable to the person or persons entitled thereto under the ordinary rules of his service if he had not`
  line `been appointed a Judge, his service as a Judge being treated as service therein for the purpose of`
  line `calculating that gratuity.]`
  line
  line `(3) The rules, notifications and orders for the time being in force with respect to the grant of deathcum-retirement`
  line `gratuity benefit to or in relation to an officer of the Central Civil Services, Class I`
  line `(including the provisions relating to deductions from pension for the purpose) shall apply to or in relation`
  line `to the grant of death-cum-retirement gratuity benefit to or in relation to a Judge who, being in service on`
  line `or after the 1st day of October, 1974, retires, or dies in circumstances to which section 17 does not apply,`
  line `subject to the modifications that`
  line
  line `(i) the minimum qualifying service for the purpose of entitlement to the gratuity shall be two`
  line `years and six months;`
  line
  line `(ii) the amount of gratuity shall be calculated on the basis of ^11[ten days'] salary for ^12[each`
  line `completed six months period] of service as a Judge; ^13***`
  line
  line `^14* * * * *`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In ^15`
  line `[sub-section (3)], the expression Judge has the same meaning as in section 14.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 50 of 1961, s. 3 (retrospectively).`
  line
  line `2. Section 17A renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 35 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1974).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 38 of 1986, s. 3, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 1-11-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2003, s. 2, for sixty per cent. of the pension admissible to him (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `5. The words /"plus fifty per cent. of his dearness pay" omitted by Act 23 of 2009, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-1-2006).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 7 of 2003, s. 2, for "and thereafter at the rate of half of the family pension so admissible" (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 46 of 2005, s. 2, for "and thereafter at the rate of thirty per cent. of his salary subject to a minimum of three`
  line `hundred and seventy-five rupees per months" (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `8. The words "plus thirty per cent. of his dearness pay subject to a minimum of one thousand nine hundred and thirteen rupees`
  line `per month" omitted by Act 23 of 2009, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-1-2006).`
  line
  line `9. The proviso inserted by Act 7 of 2003, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `10.The words and figures "Part II or" omitted by Act 13 of 2016, s. 11 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 7 of 1999, s. 4, for "twenty days" (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "each completed year" (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `13. The word and omitted by 20 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-1986).`
  line
  line `14. Clause (iii) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-1986).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 38 of 1986, s. 3, for "sub-sections (2) and (3)" (w.e.f. 1-11-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_b:
  sectionId (24195)
  sectionNo 17B
  orderNo 23
  title `Additional quantum of pension or family pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24195&sectionno=17B&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_17_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[17B. Additional quantum of pension or family pension. Every retired Judge or after his death,`
  line `the family, as the case may be, shall be entitled to an additional quantum of pension or family pension in`
  line `accordance with the following scale:--`
  line
  line `Age of Pensioner or family Pensioner Additional quantum of pension or family pension`
  line .
  line `From eighty years to less than eightyfive`
  line years
  line `Twenty per cent. of basic pension or family`
  line pension
  line
  line `From eighty-five years to less than`
  line `ninety years`
  line `Thirty per cent. of basic pension or family pension`
  line
  line `From ninety years to less than ninetyfive`
  line years
  line `Forty per cent. of basic pension or family pension`
  line
  line `From ninety-five years to less than`
  line `hundred years`
  line `Fifty per cent. of basic pension or family pension`
  line
  line `From hundred years or more Hundred per cent. of basic pension or family`
  line pension.]
  line
  line `^2[Explanation: —For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that any entitlement for additional quantum of pension or family pension shall be, and shall be deemed always to have been, from the first day of the month in which the pensioner or family pensioner completes the age specified in the first column of the scale.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2009, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-1-2006).`
  line
  line `2.Ins. by Act 44 of 2021, s. 2 (w.e.f. 18-12-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (24196)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 24
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24196&sectionno=18&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `[Conversion of sterling pension into rupees.] Omitted by the High Court and the Supreme Court`
  line `Judges (Salaries and Conditions of Service) Amendment Act, 2016 (13 of 2016), s. 12 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (24197)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 25
  title `Commutation of Pensions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24197&sectionno=19&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Civil Pensions (Commutation) Rules for the time being in`
  line `force shall, with necessary modifications, apply to Judges.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (24198)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 26
  title `Provident Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24198&sectionno=20&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Every Judge shall be entitled to subscribe to the General Provident Fund`
  line `(Central Services):`
  line
  line `Provided that a Judge who ^1`
  line `*** has held any other pensionable civil post under the Union or a State`
  line `shall continue to subscribe to the Provident Fund to which he was subscribing before his appointment as a`
  line `Judge:`
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "is a member of the Indian Civil Service or" omitted by Act 13 of 2016, s. 13 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `2. The second proviso omitted by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (24199)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 27
  title `Deposit Linked Insurance Scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 38 of 1986, s. 4 (w.e.f. 5-9-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24199&sectionno=20A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[20A.Deposit Linked Insurance Scheme.—The Deposit Linked Insurance Scheme for the time`
  line `being in force under the General Provident Fund (Central Services) Rules, 1960, shall apply to every`
  line `Judge whether he subscribes to the General Provident Fund (Central Services) or any other Provident`
  line `Fund referred to in section 20].`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (24200)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 28
  title `Authority competent to grant pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24200&sectionno=21&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Save as may be otherwise expressly provided in the`
  line `relevant rules relating to the grant of extraordinary pensions and gratuities, the authority competent to`
  line `grant pension to a Judge under the provisions of this Act shall be the President of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (24201)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 29
  title `Travelling allowances to a Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24201&sectionno=22&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Every Judge shall receive such reasonable allowances to`
  line `reimburse him for expenses incurred in travelling on duty within the territory of India and shall be`
  line `afforded such reasonable facilities in connection with travelling as may, from time to time, be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (24202)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 30
  title `Facility of rent-free houses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24202&sectionno=22A&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[A. Facility of rent-free houses.--(1) Every Judge shall be entitled without payment of rent to the`
  line `the use of an official residence in accordance with such rules as may, from time to time, be made in this`
  line behalf.
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Where a Judge does not avail himself of the use of an official residence, he may be paid every`
  line `month an allowance equivalent to an amount of twenty-four per centum of the salary which shall be`
  line `increased at the rate of--`
  line
  line `(a) twenty-seven per centum, when Dearness Allowance crosses twenty-five per centum; and`
  line
  line `(b) thirty per centum, when Dearness Allowance crosses fifty per centum].`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-10-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2018, s. 3, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_b:
  sectionId (24203)
  sectionNo 22B
  orderNo 31
  title `Conveyance facilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24203&sectionno=22B&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[22B.Conveyance facilities.—Every Judge shall be entitled to a staff car and ^2`
  line `[two hundred litres of`
  line `of fuel every month] or the actual consumption of fuel per month, whichever is less.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1986, s. 5, for sub-sections 22B and 22C (w.e.f. 1-11-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1996, s. 4, for "one hundred and fifty liters of petrol every month or the actual consumption of Petrol"`
  line `(w.e.f. 11-1-1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_c:
  sectionId (24204)
  sectionNo 22C
  orderNo 32
  title `Sumptuary allowance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24204&sectionno=22C&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_22_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[22C.Sumptuary allowance.--The Chief Justice and each of the other Judges of every High Court`
  line `shall be entitled to a sumptuary allowance of ^2[thirty-four thousand" and "twenty-seven thousand] rupees`
  line `per month respectively.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2009, s. 6, for section 22C (w.e.f. 1-1-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2018, s. 4, for "fifteen thousand" and "twelve thousand" (w.e.f. 22-9-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_d:
  sectionId (24205)
  sectionNo 22D
  orderNo 33
  title `Exemption from liability to pay income-tax on certain perquisites received by a Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24205&sectionno=22D&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_22_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[22D.Exemption from liability to pay income-tax on certain perquisites received by a Judge.—Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961),—`
  line
  line `(a) the value of rent-free official residence provided to a Judge under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `22A or the allowance paid to him under sub-section (2) of that section;`
  line
  line `(b) the value of the conveyance facilities provided to a Judge under section 22B;`
  line
  line `(c) the sumptuary allowance provided to a Judge under section 22C;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(d) the value of leave travel concession provided to a judge and members of his family,]`
  line
  line `shall not be included in the computation of his income chargeable under the head "Salaries" under section`
  line `15 of the Income- tax Act 1961 (43 of 1961).]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1988, s. 3, for section 22D (w.e.f. 1-11-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 2 of 1994, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (24206)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 34
  title `Facilities for medical treatment and other conditions of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24206&sectionno=23&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Judge and the`
  line `members of his family shall be entitled to such facilities for medical treatment and for accommodation in`
  line `hospitals as may, from time to time, be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The conditions of service of a Judge for which no express provision has been made in this Act`
  line `shall be such as may be determined by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall be deemed to have come into force on the 26th January, 1950 and any rule made`
  line `under this section may be made so as to be retrospective to any date not earlier than the commencement`
  line `of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (24207)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 35
  title `Vacation of High Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1958, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24207&sectionno=23A&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[23A. Vacation of High Courts.—(1) Every High Court shall have a vacation or vacations for such`
  line `period or periods as may, from time to time, be fixed by the President, by order notified in this behalf in`
  line `the Official Gazette, and every such order shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other law, rule or order regulating the vacation of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_b:
  sectionId (24208)
  sectionNo 23B
  orderNo 36
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24208&sectionno=23B&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content:
  string
  line `[Special provisions in respect of continuing Judges.]Omitted by the High Court and the Supreme`
  line `Court Judges (Salaries and Conditions of Service) Amendment Act, 2016 (13 of 2016), s. 14 (w.e.f. 5-4-`
  line `2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23_c:
  sectionId (24209)
  sectionNo 23C
  orderNo 37
  title `Special provisions in respect of Judges transferred from the High Court of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1964, s. 3 (w.e.f. 20-5-1954).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24209&sectionno=23C&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[23C. Special provisions in respect of Judges transferred from the High Court of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir.(1) In the calculation of service for pension of a Judge of the High Court of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir transferred to any other High Court, his service for pension as a Judge of the High Court of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir shall also be reckoned as service for pension under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In the calculation of the amount of leave at the credit of a Judge of the High Court of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir transferred to any other high Court, the amount of leave due to him as a Judge of the High Court`
  line `of Jammu and Kashmir shall be added to the amount of leave at his credit under this Act.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 23C.--Omit`
  line
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020,`
  line `notification No. S.O. 1123(E), dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation`
  line `(Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_d:
  sectionId (24210)
  sectionNo 23D
  orderNo 38
  title `Medical facilities for retired Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 1976, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-10-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24210&sectionno=23D&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_23_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[23D. Medical facilities for retired Judges.—(1) Every retired Judge shall, with effect from the`
  line `date on which the High Court Judges (Conditions of Service) Amendment Act, 1976 (35 of 1976)`
  line `receives the assent of the President, be entitled, for himself and his family, to the same facilities as`
  line `respects medical treatment and on the same conditions as a retired officer of the Central Civil Services,`
  line `Class I, and his family, are entitled under any rules and orders of the Central Government for the time`
  line `being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) but subject to such conditions and`
  line `restrictions as the Central Government may impose, a retired Judge of the High Court for a State may`
  line `avail, for himself and his family, any facilities for medical treatment which the Government of that State`
  line `may extend to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (24211)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24211&sectionno=24&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) leave of absence of a Judge;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(aa) the number of casual leaves and the conditions subject to which it may be allowed under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 3;]`
  line
  line `(b) pension payable to a Judge;`
  line
  line `(c) travelling allowances to a Judge;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ca) use of official residence by a Judge under sub-section (1) of section 22A;]`
  line
  line `(d) facilities for medical treatment and other conditions of service of a Judge;`
  line
  line `(e) any other manner which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 15 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 35 of 1976, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-10-1974).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-10-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (24212)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 40
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429&sectionId=24212&sectionno=25&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00013_195428_1517807322429
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `[Savings.]Omitted by the High Court and the Supreme Court Judges (Salaries and Conditions of`
  line `Service) Amendment Act, 2016 (13 of 2016), s. 16 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
